msg: GEOMETRY-14: updating QuaternionRotation to use Quaternion from commons-numbers
GEOMETRY-14: updates to QuaternionRotation based on changes in Quaternion from commons-numbers
GEOMETRY-14: Move "slerp" algorithm into its own class.

GEOMETRY-14: Decouple "slerp" from "rotation".

It avoids recomputations when several interpolation steps are needed.

Combined creation/transform method removed and unit test adapted.
Typo in unit test class name.
GEOMETRY-14: adding Rotation3D and AffineTransformMatrix interfaces

Upgrade dependencies.

Build now passes on JDK 10.  Thanks to Stefan Bodewig.
minor cleanup: removing unused internal methods, using better test names, adding javadocs
GEOMETRY-31: standardizing method names with commons-numbers
GEOMETRY-31: renaming dotProduct to dot and crossProduct to cross
GEOMETRY-39: Removing unneeded checks on PlaneAngleRadians normalization output
GEOMETRY-38: fixing issue where PolyhedronsSet.firstIntersection does not detect intersections on subhyperplane boundaries

GEOMETRY-40: Fix template file (web site).

Thanks to Sven Rathgeber for pointing out the copy/paste mistakes.
GEOMETRY-11: replacing double tolerance values with DoublePrecisionContext class
GEOMETRY-43 adds a test -> line intersecting cube. Line lies on plane. One intersection only.
GEOMETRY-41: Adding equals(EuclideanVector, DoublePrecisionContext) and isZero(DoublePrecisionContext) methods to EuclideanVector and subclasses
GEOMETRY-11: using shorter and more consistent method names for DoublePrecisionContext
GEOMETRY-43: adding extra condition to Plane.firstIntersection() to avoid returning facets that are parallel to the test line
GEOMETRY-42: Adding Vector2D.signedArea(Vector2D) method; removing Vector2D.cross() method since the cross product is not defined in two dimensions
GEOMETRY-27: refactoring and cleaning up OrientedPoint class; adding GeometryValueException to encapsulate idea of a programatically correct input that evaluates to an invalid geometric value
GEOMETRY-28: Cleaning up o.a.c.geometry.euclidean.twod.Line API and adding additional unit tests
GEOMETRY-29 replaces removes redundant method: calculateW.
GEOMETRY-29 corrects comment for copy factory method, corrects typo. Removes factory method with all arguments supplied.
GEOMETRY-29 rename fromThreePoints to fromPoints, corrects typos. adds getW, adds getOriginOffset, renames fromTwoVectors to fromPlaneVectors.
GEOMETRY-29 first Version of api according jira issue. Adds equals/toString to Line, adds areCoplanar to Vector3D, adds some tests.
GEOMETRY-29 removes my alternative version (probably slower) of contains(Plane).
GEOMETRY-29 working on Matts review. Part II
GEOMETRY-29 working on Matts review. Part III
GEOMETRY-29 makes {{origin}} computed instead of stored. Makes {{areCoplanar}} a private helper method in {{Plane}}.
GEOMETRY-29 fixes errors in Plane and Line reported by checkstyle.
Added a failing test case for welzlencloser corresponding to bug report [GEOMETRY-58]

Added a proposed fix for [GEOMETRY-58]

The moveToFrontBall method will disregard any point if it is within
(radius + precision.getMaxZero()) of current center.
Therefore, we might end up with a resulting radius somewhat larger than
the original author expected. To overcome this issue, we change the
comparison to something that respects the configured precision.
Use HTTPS to access Apache resources.
Replace Apache HTTP URL with HTTPS version.
Fix the site's source repository link.
GEOMETRY-59: adding Plane.fromPoints(Collection, DoublePrecisionContext) to help fix issues with computed Plane orientation
Update "pom.xml" (based on the one for "Commons RNG").
Prefer get methods over use of super

Fix unit vector test precision

(Also fixes several nearby instances of spurious whitespace)

Enable CheckStyle (based on the configuration for "Commons RNG").

"validate" requirement is commented out as it would currently fail the build.

GEOMETRY-61: Improvement of "normalize" functionality for class "Vector1D".

"Unit" class defines factory methods "from" to create a normalized instance.

GEOMETRY-61: Improvement of "normalize" functionality for class "Vector2D".

"Unit" class defines factory methods "from" to create a normalized instance.

GEOMETRY-61: Improvement of "normalize" functionality for class "Vector3D".

"Unit" class defines factory methods "from" to create a normalized instance.
GEOMETRY-61: Advertize specific characteristics of returned instance.

GEOMETRY-64: Parent class must not refer to subclass during its initialization.

Constants for unit vectors defined in "Unit" subclass.

Badge for "SonarQube".

File encoding changed to "unix".
GEOMETRY-32: refactoring BSP and related classes; also addresses issues GEOMETRY-32 (simplify Transform interface), GEOMETRY-33 (Region API), and GEOMETRY-34 (SubHyperplane optimized implementations)

msg: adding documentation to checkstyle suppression rules

Use dedicated method to check whether a "List" is empty.

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".

Use more specific interface from the JDK.

Reported by "soundcloud.io".
Zero is zero, whatever the scale.

Removed "onCut" check which at that point is always "true".

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".

Avoid several method having identical implementation.

Aliases should call the "primary" method.

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".

Anonymous inner class replaced with lambda.

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".

Prefer method reference (over lambda).

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".
Previous version fails to compile on Java 8 (although it passes on Java 11).

Standard order for assertions arguments (JUnit).

First argument is the expected value, second argument is the actual value.

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".

Order of arguments in unit tests.

Reported by "sonarcloud.io".
Removed usage of constants prefixed with "MINUS".

Update coveralls config.

Removed the manipulation of the <maven.buildNumber.timestampFormat>
property used by the buildnumber maven plugin. This will now default to
using EpochMillis.
Removed unused property to set the coveralls timestamp.
GEOMETRY-69: adding return value to BSPTreeVisitor.visit(BSPTree.Node) so that visit operations can terminate early
adding toString() tests to increase code coverage
adding test coverage for VectorXD.Unit.from(VectorXD) methods; using better assertions for ConvexSubPlane and SubPlane toString() unit tests
GEOMETRY-69: shortening nested BSPTreeVisitor enum names; shortening AbstractBSPTree tree visitor method names
GEOMETRY-16: removing custom GeometryException hierarchy and replacing with standard JDK exceptions

msg: miscellaneous cleanup and code coverage improvements
GEOMETRY-66: removing unused argument in QuaternionRotation euler angles methods
GEOMETRY-51: adding check for invalid epsilon value in EpsilonDoublePrecisionContext constructor; also making Serializable per Spotbugs report
GEOMETRY-63: small changes based on sonarcloud report: using method references instead of lambdas and moving internal methods to the classes that use them
GEOMETRY-62: fixing checkstyle issues in unit tests and enabling checkstyle validation during build
GEOMETRY-45: renaming packages in hull and enclosing modules to avoid duplicating root 'euclidean' package
adding back portion of userguide lost in merge; fixing table of contents link
GEOMETRY-72: adding BoundarySource interface and implementations in Euclidean 2D, 3D and spherical 2D; making a number of internal BSP tree classes private

GEOMETRY-75: Performance Module
Update PMD rules to be more lenient.

Disable PMD failOnViolation.

After upgrading PMD a lot of errors have now been found.
Remove redundant report goals from after success

Add profile for the examples module.

Ensure rat:check and checkstyle:check are run by travis.

Update PMD rules

Allow 'NaN' as constant name.
Relax utility class pattern.
Allow short method names.

Update spotbugs dependency for java 13 support.

Added spotbugs dependency to use 4.0.0

Remove jxr version control.

The project contains no java 9 modules so there is no requirement to
restrict JXR to a version that does not fork the build.

Allow openjdk-ea to fail.

Currently java 14 fails to run spotbugs:check.
The spotbugs plugin (3.1.12) depends on a groovy version that uses
reflection to access a private method that was removed in Java 14.

The same bug prevented gradle from working on JDK 14:
https://github.com/gradle/gradle/issues/10248

Update tests using fixed seeds for Commons RNG

seeds will create a different RNG state.

- Vector3DTest.testDotProduct_accuracy

Update release howto with push of single tag

ConvexHullBuilderTest

Fix Documentation test as the order of vertices changed.

Rename variables and deleted unnecessary assignment.

quadrilaterals. Valid points are not dismissed anymore.

Since the given Collection of points is a PointSet equivalent points are
already filtered out.

GEOMETRY-144

Cases are not needed since the given Collection of points is a PointSet.

GEOMETRY-144

The comparator guarantees, that the distance to the former point is
always greater than to the last.

Better caching for quadrilateral and parameter quadrilateralPoints

Init variable at later point.
